name: Level 7
description: Our group is dedicated to reducing plastic waste and promoting action driven change. We are working to create a fully functional plastic recycling and manufacturing center at the University of Alberta.

name: UASU Audit Committee
description: The committee is responsible for reviewing all Students' Union and Student Group financial statements, credit card expenditures, election results, and alterations to the Students' Union budget.

name: 5 Days for the Homeless
description: 5 Days for the Homeless is a student-led campaign with a mission to raise awareness and donations for Youth Empowerment and Support Services (YESS), a local charity focused on youth homelessness prevention and support for homeless youth.

name: ABBEDAM
description: ABBEDAM Productions is an extra-curricular production company made up of a majority of BA, BA (Honours), BEd, and MA drama students. Our mandate is to produce a student run production in the Second Playing Space of the Timms Centre, annually.

name: Active Minds at University of Alberta
description: Active Minds is a student led mental health awareness and advocacy group that is established for the expressed purposes of, and exists on campus to spread awareness about Mental Health through a variety of campus wide events, programs and initiatives.

name: Advocating for Children's Education
description: ACE believes in education for all. We provide educational tools and resources to schools & local organizations and emphasize the importance of education in every child's life. Follow us on instagram: @ace_ualberta

name: Agricultural, Food and Nutritional Science Graduate Student's Association
description: The Agricultural, Food and Nutritional Science Graduate Student's Association (AFNS GSA) is a representative body of all graduate students in the Department of Agricultural, Food and Nutritional Science.

name: Agricultural, Life and Environmental Sciences Graduate Students' Association
description: ALES GSA exists at the University of Alberta for the purpose of promoting its mission and goals and providing graduate students and post-docs with the opportunity for involvement, leadership, service, and professional experience.

name: Ahmadiyya Muslim Students' Association
description: The student branch of the Ahmadiyya Muslim Community in Edmonton.

name: AIESEC in Edmonton
description: AIESEC in Edmonton is a local chapter of the world's largest youth-run non-profit organization. We facilitate leadership development in youth through social volunteerships and paid professional internships.
